  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Interventional study in patients with ICD. Controlled, open intervention with exercise
      training. Assessment of changes in physiological and psychological parameters.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      ICD therapy with DC shock is associated with impaired quality of life and development of
      anxiety and depression. In a selected group of patients with ICD the intervention with
      organized high intensity training is evaluated. Peak VO2, inflammatory profile, performed
      interventions by the ICD and psychological profile is assessed. In addition a qualitative
      evaluation using interviews is performed.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
